sql:
SELECT SUM(o.quantity_ordered * p.price) AS total_revenue
FROM orders o
INNER JOIN products p ON o.product_id = p.product_id;

external_knowledge:
Running low on stock means the current quantity available is below the reorder level; high demand is defined as total demand exceeding 100 units. The ranking is based on the remaining stock levels, with the lowest stock levels receiving the lowest ranks.;

The supplier details include the name of the supplier company associated with each product.;

High demand indicates the product is popular and may require attention to ensure adequate stock levels.;

Low stock products are those where the available quantity has fallen below a predetermined level, the reorder level, indicating that a restock might be necessary.;

The ranking system helps to prioritize which products to reorder based on their current stock levels. Products with the lowest ranks are the ones in most urgent need of restocking.;

The total demand is a measure of how many units of each product have been ordered, which gives insight into the popularity and sales performance of the product.;

sql:
SELECT product_id, model, quantity_available
FROM products
ORDER BY quantity_available DESC;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_products_needing_reorder
FROM products
WHERE quantity_available <= reorder_level;

SELECT DISTINCT product_id
FROM inventory_logs
WHERE quantity_changed < 0;
